      <hedline>
        <hl1>Conservatively Speaking</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ted C Soderberg letter praises William F Buckley for not being afraid of what others think (July 11 interview)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I enjoyed Deborah Solomon's questions (July 11) for the king of conservatism. Good for William F. Buckley. He shoots straight from the hip, and he isn't afraid of what other people think. I only wonder if he authorized that disheveled picture you printed.</p>
        <p>Ted C. Soderberg  San Francisco</p>
      </block>
